-- Turkey's Akbank says plans foreign borrowing of up to $4 bln 
-- By Humeyra Pamuk
-- Tue Nov 18, 2014 10:34AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Nov 18 (Reuters) - Turkey's Akbank <AKBNK.IS> is planning to borrow up to $4 billion from international markets, the bank said on Tuesday.

The borrowing instruments will be in varying maturities, the bank said in a stock exchange filing.